//Category 1 Alamak is used when expressing realisation of forgetfulness.\nE.g. Xiao Ming exclaimed, \'Alamak! I forgot to bring my wallet today!\'
Bodoh is used to refer to someone dumb or forgetful. It is not extremely insulting, however.\nE.g. Ali called out to Xiao Ming, \'Oi, you forgot to bring your money today again ah?\'
//Category 2 Ayam Penyet means \'smashed chicken\' in Javanese. Originating from Java, Indonesia, this dish is prepared by smashing fried chicken with the pestle against mortar to make it softer, and served with sambal, slices of cucumbers, fried tofu and tempeh.
